FBIS4-63343 "drsov099_a_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-099 Daily Report 23 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Foreign Ministry: No Objection to UN Reviewing Crimea Issue Foreign Ministry: No Objection to UN Reviewing Crimea Issue LD2305091694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 23 May 94 LD2305091694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] Galina Sidorova, political advisor to the Russian foreign minister, said Moscow has no objection to the Crimean issue being reviewed in the United Nations. This is what Ukraine wants, Sidorova told journalists in Murmansk. Russia, Galina Sidorova stressed, wants Kiev and Simferopol to settle all contentions using exclusively political methods, INTERFAX reports.
